  "title" : "I am not able to build android app in Unity3D. Error Gradle initialization failed",
  "body" : "<p>I am using an empty Unity Android project. I am not able to build APK since 2 weeks. I am getting this error</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>CommandWithNoStdoutInvokationFailure: Gradle initialization failed.\n  UnityEditor.Android.Command.RunWithShellExecute (System.String command, System.String args, System.String workingdir, System.String errorMsg) (at &lt;4132c5c2cd7b45b09ef33302ae416489>:0)\n  UnityEditor.Android.AndroidJavaTools.RunJavaWithShellExecute (System.String args, System.String workingdir, System.String error) (at &lt;4132c5c2cd7b45b09ef33302ae416489>:0)</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Here is the full Error: </p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/tre0n.png\" alt=\"Error Image\"></p>\n\n<p>I am not getting any solution on the internet as in Latest version of Unity 2019.1.6f1, JDK, Android SDK and NDK are installed within Unity (installed while installing Unity).</p>\n\n<p>I have installed new Windows 10 in my another Drive and Installed same Unity Version in the new Windows 10. And it built successfully without any issue. However I am not able to build it on my current Operation System. Please help.</p>\n"
